<h2 id="current-large-multi-investigator-projects">Current large multi investigator projects</h2>

<p><strong><a href="https://www.nsf.gov/awardsearch/showAward?AWD_ID=2025515&amp;HistoricalAwards=false">National Science Foundation - The rules of microbiota colonization of the mammalian gut</a></strong>
<br />
‚ÄúThis project has three main thrusts: 1) Learn microbial community-level rules that quantitatively predict population dynamics of mouse gut colonization and assess these rules across differing ranges of microbial diversity and composition, 2) Elucidate microbial gene-level mechanisms that predict mouse gut colonization dynamics, and 3) Profile microbial spatiotemporal organization and dynamics during gut colonization at the species and gene level to predict microbial community dynamics.‚Äù</p>

